  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 52, 47.359231}", 
    "history" -> {"14.0", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"quantum entropy", "Bravyi theorem"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "BravyiEntanglementEntropy[grn, [k1, k2, ...]] returns the entanglement \
entropy between the subsystem consisting of fermion modes {k1, k2, ...} \
\\[Subset] {1, 2, ..., n} in the Bravyi state characterized by n*n matrix grn \
of single-particle Green's functions. \
BravyiEntanglementEntropy[NambuGreen[{grn, anm}], {k1, k2, ...}] or \
BravyiEntanglementEntropy[{grn, anm}, [k1, k2, ...}] returns the entanglement \
entropy in the Bravyi state characterized by n*n matrices grn and anm of \
normal and anomalous Green's functions, respectively. \
BravyiEntanglementEntropy[state, {k1, k2, ...}] is equivalent to \
BravyiEntanglementEntropy[BravyiGreen[state, {k1, k2, ...}], {k1, k2, ...}] \
for Bravyi state. BravyiEntanglementEntropy[{k1, k2, ...}] is an operator \
form of BravyiEntanglementEtropy to be applied to Green's functions or Bravyi \
states.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
    "BravyiEntanglementEntropy", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> 
    "", "windowtitle" -> "BravyiEntanglementEntropy", "type" -> "Symbol", 
    "uri" -> "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/BravyiEntanglementEntropy"}},
